      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BAHAMA BAY (2) just missed here this grade before the spell and was too good for the 70 graders over 1200m first-up. Flies second-up and can go on with the job. THROW AT DA STUMPS (4) disappointed in the same contest but his efforts two and four back stack up. Maps well and he'd be a chance bringing his A-game. O'TYCOON (1) has raced twice in Open grade since returning from South Australia and will be better for them. His best form stacks up and expect more from him today in easier and with the blinkers applied for the first time. FAST FREEZE (5) is an op-pacer drawn low and would be a hope if presented forward this time around. Todd rides and that's a decent push for her chances. DOWN THE WICKET (3) got close this grade last time and has been freshened. Worth keeping onside.",
